result.name: Khana Khazana Indian Vegetarian Restaurant and Bar

Khana Khazana Indian Vegetarian Restaurant and Bar
Khana Khazana Indian Vegetarian Restaurant and Bar
Khana Khazana Indian Vegetarian Restaurant and Bar

reviews.text:
Super Amazing Food

By far one of thr best restaurants we have been to..
Nan was fresh, soft and super tasty. Every item was good. My wife and I loved it.

For Indian food this is a must go. Don't be fooled by the relatively modest interior.

It's the best Indian restaurant in Hong Kong.
The food taste is authentic Indian.
Nice and clean with good ambiance and music.
Pure Vegetarian, which is quite difficult to find in Hong Kong.
I loved the taste of Sambhar and I'm not even from southern India.
Very good place to go with colleagues and friends who want to try Indian cuisine.
Lunch buffet on weekdays is 120 HKD and on weekends, it's 154 HKD.
It's worth every penny.
Great Indian food. Had dinner here 2 weeks ago and I have been back twice. Near where I stay so it's really convenient

Staff was good, cultery, curtains wer good, food presentation was very nice very tempting but there was no taste in food. I order 5 dishes and surprisingly not even a single dish was good. So I am not going again over there.

Maybe I'm biased because I love Indian cuisine and homemade comfort food, but I really enjoyed my buffet lunch. The food was great, it didn't make me feel tired and thirsty, and the staff was so friendly and helpful towards my guest and I - will definitely be returning for another bite 😁
